# backend/.env.test — test-runner configuration (loaded by conftest.py before .env).
#
# Copy to backend/.env.test (gitignored) and uncomment the test-runner
# toggles you want. scripts/run-tests.sh sources this file when present.
#
# Phase 11a CI-debt (2026-05-12): per CLAUDE.md, runtime application
# settings + secrets live in the DB (app_config + app_secrets, Fernet-
# encrypted), not in .env. This file ONLY holds toggles that the test
# runner itself reads (pytest skipif markers, etc.) — never application
# credentials. Broker / CF Access / Schwab / Alpaca / Futu creds are
# seeded into the prod DB via the admin API and copied from prod →
# test_postgres at test-run time by scripts/db/copy-prod-creds-to-test-pg.sh.

# ── Database ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Always point pytest at the dedicated test container, never the prod NUC.
# CI workflows override this via workflow env: blocks.
# DATABASE_URL=postgresql+asyncpg://test:test@localhost:5433/test

# ── Test-runner toggles ──────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Real Redis fidelity test (vs fakeredis). Hits docker compose redis:7.
# The CI_REDIS_URL password matches REDIS_PASSWORD in the main .env;
# extract via: docker compose exec backend bash -c 'echo $REDIS_URL'
# CI_USE_REAL_REDIS=1
# CI_REDIS_URL=redis://:CHANGE_ME@redis:6379/0

# Real-Schwab integration tests (test_real_schwab_smoke). Needs
# Schwab creds already seeded into the prod DB (via PUT /api/admin/
# secrets/broker/schwab.*). The flag itself just opts in.
# CI_USE_REAL_SCHWAB=1
